### Verdict: REQUEST_CHANGES

### Summary
WRK-1008 is not safe to merge as-is. I found one confirmed regression in `submit-to-codex.sh` that breaks normal success flows in constrained environments, and one hard-gate policy bypass risk in `cross-review.sh` from the provided logic. Test coverage is improved but does not yet guard these paths.

### Issues Found
- [P1] Renderer fallback regression: `run_renderer()` prefers `uv` whenever present and does not fall back to `python3` if `uv run` fails. In environments where `uv` exists but cannot run (for example cache permission issues), successful Codex JSON responses are downgraded to raw output with exit 6, causing false hard-gate failures. File: [submit-to-codex.sh](/mnt/local-analysis/workspace-hub/scripts/review/submit-to-codex.sh). Repro: `bash scripts/review/tests/test-submit-to-codex-robustness.sh` failed 4 cases (`success path exits zero`, `success rendered verdict`, and retry equivalents) due this path.
- [P1] Hard-gate bypass risk in the provided `cross-review.sh` logic: non-zero Codex runs classified as `NO_OUTPUT` are allowed into fallback consensus. In the provided content, `# Codex CLI not found` also classifies as `NO_OUTPUT`, so `all` mode can pass via 2-of-3 fallback even when Codex is not installed. That weakens the stated hard-gate contract. File: [cross-review.sh](/mnt/local-analysis/workspace-hub/scripts/review/cross-review.sh), classifier dependency in [validate-review-output.sh](/mnt/local-analysis/workspace-hub/scripts/review/validate-review-output.sh).
- [P2] Coverage gap: tests do not explicitly assert renderer runtime fallback behavior (`uv` present but failing, `python3` available) and do not explicitly enforce “Codex CLI missing must remain hard-block in all mode.” Current suites: `test-codex-fallback.sh` and `test-cross-review-path-sanitization.sh` pass, but they miss these regression-prone cases.

### Suggestions
- Fix `run_renderer()` to attempt `uv run ...` first, then fall back to `python3` on non-zero exit (not just on missing command).
- In `cross-review.sh`, explicitly treat `# Codex CLI not found` (and optionally other local setup failures) as hard-block, never fallback-eligible.
- Add tests: (1) mocked failing `uv` + working `python3` should still return 0 with rendered markdown, (2) `all` mode with Codex CLI missing must exit non-zero even if Claude/Gemini are APPROVE/MINOR.
- After fixes, rerun: `bash scripts/review/tests/test-submit-to-codex-robustness.sh && bash scripts/review/tests/test-codex-fallback.sh && bash scripts/review/tests/test-cross-review-path-sanitization.sh`.

### Questions for Author
- Do you want fallback to remain allowed for transport/timeouts only, or for any `NO_OUTPUT` class? The current policy text and behavior should be made explicit and test-locked.
